Package: kdetoys
Architecture: all
Section: kde
Depends: amor (>= ${source:Version}), kteatime (>= ${source:Version}), kworldclock (>= ${source:Version})
Description: toys from the official KDE 4 release
 KDE (the K Desktop Environment) is a powerful Open Source graphical
 desktop environment for Unix workstations. It combines ease of use,
 contemporary functionality, and outstanding graphical design with the
 technological superiority of the Unix operating system.
 .
 This metapackage includes a collection of toys and fun extras provided
 with the official release of KDE 4.


Package: amor
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: kwin
Suggests: khelpcenter
Description: a KDE creature for your desktop
 AMOR stands for Amusing Misuse Of Resources. It provides several different
 characters who prance around your X screen doing tricks and giving you tips.
 .
 This package is part of KDE, and a component of the KDE 4 toys module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdetoys' packages for more information.

Package: kteatime
Architecture: any
Section: kde
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Suggests: khelpcenter
Description: KDE 4 utility for making a fine cup of tea
 KTeaTime is a handy timer for steeping tea. No longer will you have to
 guess at how long it takes for your tea to be ready. Simply select the
 type of tea you have, and it will alert you when the tea is ready to
 drink.
 .
 KTeaTime sits in the KDE system tray.
 .
 Please note that KTeaTime is written explicitly for KDE. If you are
 using a non-KDE window manager or desktop environment then it is quite
 possible that KTeaTime will not work on your system.
 .
 This package is part of KDE, and a component of the KDE 4 toys module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdetoys' packages for more information.

Package: kworldclock
Architecture: any
Section: games
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Suggests: kdeartwork-misc, kdesktop, khelpcenter
Provides: kworldwatch
Description: earth watcher for KDE 4
 Displays where in the world it is light and dark depending on time, as
 well as offering the time in all of the major cities of the world.
 This can be run standalone, as an applet in the KDE panel or as a
 desktop background.
 .
 Additional kworldclock themes are available in the kdeartwork-misc package.
 .
 This package is part of KDE, and a component of the KDE 4 toys module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdetoys' packages for more information.

Package: kdetoys-dbg
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: kdebase-runtime-dbg
Priority: extra
Description: debugging symbols for kdetoys
 This package contains the debugging symbols associated with kdetoys.
 They will automatically be used by gdb for debugging kdetoys-related
 issues.
